Pushing the knight is pretty weak when white WANTS to play Nd6+.  But white might be better off playing 9 Pb4.  The black queen is all that is protecting against the infamous Nc7+ rook fork.  Black could respond with Qb6, but white would answer with Be3, forcing the black queen back to Qd8.
If black plays Kd8 white answers NxPf7+ and forks the h rook.
Now the king must move.  Kf8 blocks the h rook.
